    • setAppointmentTable

      public static void setAppointmentTable(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> appointmentList, javafx.scene.control.TableView<Appointment> appointmentTable, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,Integer> appointmentID, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,Integer> customerID, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,Integer> userID, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,String> contactName, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,String> title, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,String> description, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,String> location, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,String> type, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,LocalDateTime> start, javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Appointment,LocalDateTime> end)
      Sets cells in table of appointments. ------------------------------------------------- LAMBDA EXPRESSION USAGE #1: ------------------------------------------------- Used a lambda expression in this method to take the value in the contact ComboBox (an int, representing the contact ID), and convert it into the contact name. This made it much easier to populate the Customer cells and improved readability.
      Parameters:
      appointmentList - the list of appointments to be put into cells
      appointmentTable - the table to be filled out
      appointmentID - unique id assigned to each appointment
      customerID - unique id assigned to each customer
      userID - unique id assigned to each user
      contactName - name of each contact
      title - the title of the appointment
      description - the appointment description
      location - the location of the appointment
      type - the type of appointment
      start - the start date and time of the apppointment
      end - the end date and time of the appointment
